embeds.title: Medical Department Guidelines
embeds.description: This area describes the duties of Medical Department Personnel, how to complete them, and what rules they should follow in their pursuit of maintaining the health of all personnel within the Foundation.

embeds.title: Medical Department Ranking Structure
embeds.description: This is a comprehensive list on how the Medical Department handles its ranks.

fields.name: High Ranks
fields.value:
<>The Overseer
The Overseer acts as an overwatch on the department, making sure its duties run smoothly, and its best wishes are represented within the Council, however keeping a fairly hands-off approach. Recieves Omni clearance.

<>The Director
The Director acts as the main operational manager of the Medical Department. The Director handles most duties relating to how the Department is run and maintains direct contact to the Overseer. Recieves Level - 5 clearance.

<>The Assistant Director
The Assistant Director acts under the Director and helps implement changes within the Department with the Director, and usually helps with managing departmental personnel. Recieves Level - 4 clearance.

<>Board of Health
The Board of Health is a group of 3 individuals who have excelled in their duties to the Medical Department and now assist in making vital decisions for the Department. Recieves Level - 4 Clearance.
